Clauses.ClauseDesc:
Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, a copyright society may—
(i) issue licences under section 30 in respect of any rights under this Act;
(ii) collect fees in pursuance of such licences;
(iii) distribute such fees among author and other owners of right after making deductions for its
own expenses;
(iv) perform any other functions consistent with the provisions of section 35.
